  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining App\'s Core Function**\n\nI\'m focused on the fundamental need: tracking group meal expenses. My current priority is to solidify the basic mechanics. How can I best represent individual payments and ensure fairness in determining the next payer? I\'m thinking about the most user-friendly way to balance who owes whom.\n\n\n**Calculating Next Payer**\n\nI\'ve moved on to the payment logic; I\'ll calculate who owes what, ensuring fairness. I\'m focusing on \"who owes/who should pay next\" based on individual contributions, starting with the least paid. I\'m excited about adding the receipt upload and calorie estimate features. I need to integrate the Gemini API for receipt parsing. It\'s a nice plus to confirm the API skill is available, and understand the pattern. I\'ll integrate the server-side Gemini API. I will use the `gemini-api` skill.\n\n\n**Considering Data Persistence Options**\n\nI\'m evaluating data persistence. Initially, I considered local storage, but I now realize persistent data is essential for tracking payment history across sessions, requiring a cloud database like Firestore. The goal is to capture user-inputted content for future access. My current thought is to set up Firebase, but I\'ll make sure it\'s the right choice given the user didn\'t ask for it explicitly.\n\n\n**Analyzing Data Persistence Strategy**\n\nI\'m now diving deep into the data persistence strategy. Given the need for Gemini API interaction and a server-side component to safeguard the API key, I\'m leaning toward a full-stack Express server. This opens up options: simple JSON file persistence within the container, or local storage. We need a server-side API anyway! I\'m evaluating the trade-offs of using `firebase-integration` versus the custom Express server approach. Based on the guidelines, transient storage seems acceptable, which could be client-side with `localStorage`.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will read the `gemini-api` skill instructions to ensure I use the recommended coding patterns and SDK version for calorie estimation and receipt parsing."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 6
      nanos: 429087550
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
