  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Data Structures**\n\nI\'m now structuring the project data types in `/src/types.ts`. The focus is on clean component boundaries and server interactions by representing our model variables. I\'m carefully considering necessary data structures for clarity and maintainability.\n\n\n**Constructing Payment Logic**\n\nI\'m now diving into the payment calculation and balance management. I\'ve defined `Friend` and `Expense` data structures, including `MealItem` for finer details. Now, I\'m developing a heuristic to determine who should pay next, focusing on responsible amounts versus actual payments and working on tracking individual balances for each friend, accounting for how much they were actually responsible for. I\'m exploring how to fairly calculate and manage balances for each expense.\n\n\n**Calculating Net Balances**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the core payment logic, and am focused on calculating individual \"Net Balances.\" Each participant\'s share is the expense amount divided by the number of participants. The Net Balance, for each person, is then the total they\'ve paid minus their total share. Now I\'m working to sort friends to clearly identify who owes the most, or has paid the least total money.\n\n\n**Defining Payment Logic**\n\nI\'ve refined the net balance calculation. I\'m focusing on `totalSpent`, `totalShare`, and the `netBalance` (`totalSpent - totalShare`). I\'ve determined that the person with the lowest net balance (most negative) should pay next to minimize the standard deviation of balances, which is the fairest solution. I\'m planning to describe this clearly in the UI. I\'m also planning the file paths: `src/types.ts` for core types, `server.ts` for the Express server, and `src/App.tsx` for the interactive dashboard.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/src/types.ts` file to define the types for `Friend`, `Expense`, `MealItem`, and API integration. This will let both the server and client speak a unified language."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 726330416
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
