  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Server Setup**\n\nOkay, I\'m now focusing on the `server.ts` file. Before diving into the implementation, I want to ensure the Express server strictly adheres to guidelines. This includes binding to port 3000 and 0.0.0.0, as well as prioritizing API routes before Vite middleware. It seems important to keep this clean from the start!\n\n\n**Initializing Gemini**\n\nI\'m now integrating Gemini into the server setup. I\'m importing `GoogleGenAI` and initializing it with the API key from environment variables. I\'m using a custom `User-Agent` header for identification. The model choice is settled: `\'gemini-3.5-flash\'` is optimal for the multi-modal tasks, which is ideal! I\'m planning to craft a robust prompt that can handle images and textual item descriptions for calorie estimation from receipts.\n\n\n**Designing the API Endpoint**\n\nI\'m now designing the `/api/scan-receipt` endpoint. I\'m focusing on the POST request structure, requiring either a base64-encoded image or optional text input for flexibility. I\'m exploring the nuances of base64 parsing and structuring the image data for the Gemini model, specifically the `mimeType` and the raw data. I\'m planning to use `@google/genai`\'s `Type` to enforce a strict JSON schema for the response, ensuring predictable data output for parsing the items, prices, and calories. This will produce a consistent `ReceiptScanResult`.\n\n\n**Refining Receipt Response**\n\nI\'m now refining the JSON schema for the API response to be very clear. I\'ve focused on ensuring the `responseSchema` accurately models the data expected from the Gemini model. This includes the `title` field for a suggested meal name, the `amount` of the total cost, and a list of `items` each with a `name`, `price`, and `estimatedCalories`. The total estimated calories for the entire meal is also included. This will ensure consistent data!\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the full-stack server backend `/server.ts` with routing, Express middlewares, body parser limit configurations, Vite integration, and a `/api/scan-receipt` endpoint powered by Gemini 3.5 Flash JSON schema extraction."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 915027762
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
