  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Summarizing Our Implementation**\n\nI\'ve just finished the complete full-stack \"Meal Expense Tracker\" application, Meals Tracker, and am now focusing on crafting a concise and elegant summary. The goal is to highlight the conceptual design and features professionally, emphasizing the key elements without getting bogged down in specifics.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed building **Meals Tracker**, a modern, full-stack group meal expense tracker and calorie estimation ledger. The app combines structured financial splitting with intelligent dietary calculations.\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Design Concept (Bistro Warm Paper Theme)\n- **High-Contrast Warmth**: Styled with premium off-white canvas tones mirroring physical menus, contrasted against stone charcoal typography and soft warm orange accents.\n- **Adaptive Spacing**: Designed with fluid layouts and high-density typography pairings, giving the transaction ledger and comparison charts room to breathe.\n- **Dynamic Micro-Transitions**: Powered by responsive framer motions that animate tabs shifting, expandable entries unfolding, and receipt scan highlights appearing smoothly.\n\n---\n\n### \342\234\250 Core Features & Workflows\n\n#### 1. Fairness Smart Recommendation\n- Automatically processes total spendings against relative splits for every dining event.\n- Flags exactly who is furthest in \"group debt\" or has paid the least total out-of-pocket, giving a one-click action to log a meal for them and balance the group table.\n\n#### 2. Gemini-Powered Receipt Scan & Calorie Diagnostics\n- **Receipt Image Extraction**: Allows secure drag-and-drop or camera uploads of dining receipts. A server-side proxy route processes the document using **Gemini 3.5 Flash** to extract merchant names, item lists, and individual pricing.\n- **Nutritional Portions Valuation**: Automatically assigns realistic food portions matching the meal and estimates item calories, giving an aggregate nutritional value for the dining session.\n- **Interactive Manual Fine-Tuning**: Users can add, modify, or delete parsed dish names, adjust dollar amounts, or alter calories if they want to override the AI assumptions.\n\n#### 3. Proportional Billing & Shared Splits\n- Supports selective matching of who participated in eating a given meal.\n- Dynamically parses split rates so that non-participants are excluded from having to pay back the payer.\n- Visualizes in-depth comparison charts showing each friend\'s comparative balance bar in a clean dual-direction grid.\n\n#### 4. Sandbox Storage & Persistence\n- Automatically persists all group members, transaction forms, notes, and photos to client-side storage, ensuring no data loss occurs upon browser refresh or tab closings.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 46397131
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
